   General Overview
   [aviris_under_bar.gif]
   [spacer.gif]
   AVIRIS is an acronym for the Airborne Visible InfraRed Imaging
   Spectrometer. AVIRIS is a world class instrument in the realm of Earth
   Remote Sensing. It is a unique optical sensor that delivers calibrated
   images of the upwelling spectral radiance in 224 contiguous spectral
   channels (also called bands) with wavelengths from 400 to 2500
   nanometers (nm). The instrument flies aboard a NASA ER-2 airplane (a U2
   plane modified for increased performance) at approximately 20 km above
   sea level, at about 730 km/hr. AVIRIS has flown all across the US, plus
   Canada and Europe. [spacer.gif]
   [spacer.gif]

